cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CL 

The paper deals with feature learning for multimedia event detection, which involves computer vision (CV) and machine learning (ML) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves multiple modalities, which suggests cs.MM (Multimedia) as the second likely sub-category. The use of sparse coding and autoencoders indicates cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the third likely sub-category. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques for event detection, which suggests cs.IR as the fourth likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques for evaluating the performance of the system, which suggests cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the fifth likely sub-category.
